headline: Private Markets: Musk’s SpaceX targets 2026 IPO at valuation of $1.5T

headline: How Investors Are Reacting To L3Harris Technologies (LHX) Record GMLRS Contract And Camden Capacity Expansion
summary: L3Harris Technologies recently received a follow-on production contract worth up to US$200 million from Lockheed Martin to supply Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System Insensitive Munition propulsion units, with manufacturing centered at its new Camden, Arkansas facility that lifts annual capacity by more than 30%.
